body: In python 2.X/3.X datetime module has it's own datetime.h file in standard (C headers) library. Fast creation of date/time/datetime instances require access to C API of datetime module. Addition of datetime.pxd could resolve this problem.

commit.message: Allow setting a default encoding to ease str/unicode <-> c string conversion.
Remove datetime_ex.h in favor of defining inline functions in .pxd file
Ensure that newline is added to the end of file
Fix datetime.pxd and test datetime_pxd.pyx. Now runtests pass for datetime_pxd.pyx.

Docs for c_string_type and c_string_encoding
